CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 3, 1959, pg. A15 reads: "Junior Sorority Entertains - Chi Omega Phi Junior Sorority entertained at a party Dec. 29, at Howe Studio for over 100 guests. Pictured are some of the members of the sorority and their friends.  Left to right, seated: Willa Fountaine, chaplain, and Donna Rideout. Standing: Bea Bedell, Erlene Adair, social chairman; Carole VeLar, secretary; Richard Hancock, Karen West, Charmaine Austin, Paul Chapman, and Donna Drake, program chairman, - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of Chi Omega Phi Junior Sorority party at Howe Studio, from left to right seated: chaplain Willa Fountaine, and Donna Rideout; standing: Bea Bedell, social chairman Erlene Adair, secretary Carole VeLar, Richard Hancock wearing striped jacket, Karen West wearing eyeglasses, Charmaine Austin, Paul Chapman, and program chairman Donna Drake
